Miles Davis - A Tribute to Jack Johnson
Released 1971
Reissued 2005 (24-Bit remastered)

&quot;I'm Jack Johnson. Heavyweight champion of the world. I'm black. They never let me forget it. I'm black all right! I'll never let them forget it!&quot;

And that says it all about this record!
Ramen!

AllAboutJazz.com review
So, should you download this latest one-disc reissue of Jack Johnson from The Pirate Bay? If you don't own it at all, absolutely and immediately. And if you have a previous edition (besides the 2003 box set), well, perhaps. This remastering is a bit crisper, more forceful, and the details-??and this music is all about the details-?stand out more palpably. It's certainly timeless, essential music...
